{
  "Buffer Solutions": "缓缓解决办法",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "A student prepares a buffer by mixing 100.0 mL of 0.200 M acetic acid with 100.0 mL of 0.150 M sodium acetate (pKa = 4.74). What is the pH of this buffer?": "学生准备缓冲剂,将100.0毫升0.200M乙酸与100.0毫升0.10M乙酸(pKa = 4.74)乙酸钠(pKa = 4.74)混合起来。 这一缓冲剂的pH值是多少?",
  "After mixing, moles HA = 0.200 x 0.100 = 0.0200 mol, moles A- = 0.150 x 0.100 = 0.0150 mol. pH = 4.74 + log(0.0150/0.0200) = 4.74 + log(0.75) = 4.74 + (-0.125) = 4.62. The pH is below 4.74 because there is more weak acid than conjugate base.": "在混合后,摩尔HA=0.200x0.100=0.0200毫升,摩尔A=0.10x0.100=0.0150毫升,pH=4.74+log(0.0150/0.0200)=4.74+log(0.75)=4.74+log(-0.125)=4.62。pH值低于4.74,因为弱酸大于合金基数。",
  "A researcher adds 0.010 mol of HCl to 1.00 L of a buffer containing 0.100 mol CH3COOH and 0.100 mol CH3COO- (pKa = 4.74). What is the new pH?": "研究人员将0.100 mol CH3COOH和0.100 mol CH3COO-(pKa = 4.74)的缓冲剂添加0.010 mol HCl至1.00 L,其中含有0.100 mol CH3COOH和0.100 mol CH3COO-(pKa = 4.74)的新pH值是什么?",
  "The HCl reacts with A-: 0.010 mol H+ converts 0.010 mol A- to HA. New moles: A- = 0.100 - 0.010 = 0.090 mol; HA = 0.100 + 0.010 = 0.110 mol. pH = 4.74 + log(0.090/0.110) = 4.74 + log(0.818) = 4.74 - 0.087 = 4.65. The pH changed by only 0.09 units, demonstrating the buffer's effectiveness.": "HCl反应与A:0.010 mol H+将0.010 mol A转换为HA。新的摩尔:A=0.100 - 0.010 = 0.090 mol;HA= 0.100 + 0.010 mol. pH= 4.74 + log(0.090/0.110) = 4.74 + log(0.818) = 4.74 - 0.087 = 4.65。PH仅变化0.09 单位,表明缓冲的效果。"
}